1.演者の初期配置
2.演出開始

King Agnos: You are truly a seductress who never gets tired
no matter how many times I embrace you. The word that best
describes you is 'demonic', Caron.
Mistress Caron: I am honored to receive your praise.

King Agnos: I should have met you sooner. Well, considering
my position, there are things that can't be helped.

King Agnos: As a king, I am not a completely free entity. I
constantly engage in negotiations with the Senate to govern
the empire.

King Agnos: My marriage to my wife Leucos is also, so to
speak, a political marriage.

Mistress Caron: It is said that heroes only appear on the
battlefield, while demons appear within politics, as it has
been since ancient times.

King Agnos: That's right... It's the end for today. Please
leave now.
Mistress Caron: Understood, Lord Agnos, our king.

King Agnos: This is just between us... but my wife Leucos
may not last long.

King Agnos: Caron, the side of the throne might be
comfortable, you know?
Mistress Caron: I shall take my leave... Please excuse me.

The moment Caron received the news of her husband Heis'
death, she deeply resented King Agnos, who had issued the
order to participate in the subjugation.

Caron, the destroyer of the modest paradise we had created
ourselves. Before she knew it, a knife was gripped in
Caron's hand. It was the hunting knife that her beloved
husband Heis had cherished as a treasure.

I must kill her, as proof of my love. I accepted the
invitation to become the noble king's mistress and headed to
the royal palace. I am prepared to seek revenge no matter
what humiliation I may endure.

King Agnos welcomed Caron as his mistress and had her live
near the royal palace. For King Agnos, Caron was a presence
that made him forget about the troubles caused by the
deteriorating health of Queen Leucos and the uprising
rebels.

Caron had multiple opportunities to assassinate King Agnos.
However, if it was discovered that she was the one who
killed him, her beloved son, Luid, would also be killed.
Caron cursed her own recklessness for coming to the royal
palace without a plan.

Around a year had passed since she had been trusted as a
mistress, when unexpectedly, King Agnos uttered the words
beside the throne. And then, she heard her mother's voice
saying, Climb to the top.

Perhaps, this place is the closest to the top of the empire,
the place that my younger self and mother desired...? As
Caron's heart beats faster, the cursed blood runs through
her entire body.
Caron found herself murmuring, I might become the queen...

Caron immediately ended the war with Tarasa upon Agnos'
death. The sudden change in direction caused confusion among
the Senate and the Imperial Army, and during that chaos,
Caron strengthened her authority as queen by forming
alliances with the senators who had conspired against her.

She was someone who, despite being the queen, held power
almost equal to that of the king. It was a privilege given
only to Caron in the history of the empire. However, this
was not the pinnacle. The true pinnacle was the position of
queen itself, which belonged to Caron.

For Caron, peace and tranquility were just temporary dreams.
The days of health and calm were illusions, and the palace
where desires and conspiracies intertwined was Caron's
reality, the greatest stage where she could shine.

The knife that Heis once beautifully and carefully
maintained. It had lost its shine and was completely rusted.
Just like Caron's heart, it seemed to deny those days.

Caron threw the knife from the palace window. It was
trampled by marching soldiers, buried in the ground, and
disappeared from sight. Eventually, Caron even forgot that
she had possessed the knife.
